<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Special examinations provide students an opportunity to establish credit for certain courses. Credit may be earned by Advanced Placement Exams. To apply for credit by examination, students must complete a petition for credit by examination in the Counseling and Testing Office. A minimum of 6 semester credit hours must be earned at Brazosport College before credit will be posted to the student's transcript. A maximum of 24 hours may be earned by exam.</i>
